reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great phone case.
reviews.reviewText: Been using this case for several weeks now, it’s perfect. Holds all the cards I need (max of 3) and have not had any issues with cards slipping out (ex: when grabbing phone from pocket, phone in hand, or even vigorously shaking phone). The cards are snug.Case is also very slim, has the right amount of coverage (volume and power buttons) as well as enough bezel to protect the camera lens and screen. The textured grip is also nice, but I don’t notice it when in hand at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seems to do what is promised
reviews.reviewText: First time with this company. Case fits nicely on to the iphone 13 pro. I got it in black and it looks decent. I keep three cards in the back. They can be a little annoying to get out (like takes an extra couple of seconds to remove them vs taking them out of a wallet but the flip side is that they are in the case securely so won't go flying out if I have to pull out my phone and take a call, so it is a tradeoff I can live with. The case is not too thick but it is thick enough that when you lay it down on a desk face up the camera lens are not making contact with the desk because the case lifts the phone up just enough to prevent direct contact between the camera lenses and the surface.The case feels sturdy but thankfully I haven't dropped my phone yet so haven't had to see if the case held up. My last phone I went for over two years with no case and no screen protector. The glass on the back of the phone cracked and the camera lens got a scratch which impacted photos, hence why this phone has a case and screen protector. The sides have a decent grip to them. The only thing I do not like is the feel of the back which is very slick. I have to be very careful to make sure I am holding the sides where there is grip and not grabbing the back of the phone because I could see it slipping out of my hand easily when taking it out of my too quickly if I just grab on to the back. For the price I think it is worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love how I can have my most important cards as well as drivers license on me. The simple slim profile makes this the most convenient. It’s made with quality materials!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: i love this case because i don’t like carrying around wallets as i tend to put them down and leave them places by accident. it holds about 4 cards 5 is pushing but is doable just makes it harder to get the cards out. i’ve had this case for over a year and have had no problems with it. i also drop my phone constantly and the case has done a good job protecting it so far. 10/10 would recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this phone case!
reviews.reviewText: This case does everything I want. It's easy to hold, has been durable enough for me. Dropped it twice, only from a couple of feet, onto concrete, no damage. I carry my driver license, a bank card, one business card and a twenty dollar bill. I do keep my wallet in my car, with several other id cards that I seldom need, but this case is perfect for general use, meets my needs perfectly. Bought in February of this year, still like new. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It has saved me many times when I forgot my wallet
reviews.reviewText: This case is so practical and convenient, I used to forget my wallet at home a lot, now as long as I have my phone, I'm good to go! It is very easy to hold, it isn't bulky, however, I wish I could use a wireless charger with this (hence the 4 stars).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best phone case!
reviews.reviewText: As someone that chronically loses her purse in public places, I’ve had to resort to keeping all important cards and my license on my phone. I’ve been using a card holder that sticks to the back of your case but this is SO MUCH BETTER. It easily fits three cards, I’m sure another one would fit,as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Do you have a toddler who enjoys running around, smacking their little brother, screaming, taking things that they aren’t supposed to have and yeeting said things when they are told to give them back? Well then smack my butt and call me sally, burn your current phone case; because this is the phone case for you!My wife and I got new iPhone 13 pros today (because treat yo self!) and we decided to go with these Smartish cases simply because neither of us carry wallets or a purse (we’re millennials, get over it) and boy am I glad we did!As soon as we had a little unboxing therapy, we got the screen protectors on and the phones in our new nifty Smartish cases we decided to take a break from the phones for some family time. That family time consisted of our toddler daughter finding said phones and running around the house with them yelling “ghdfcajdkyjtvsgsjandv” when we approached her and asked her nicely for them back she looked at us with her big puppy dog eyes, summoned her inner MLB pitcher and proceeded to yeet the phones across the living room. When I picked up the phones, half expecting them to look like a Ford Pinto in a fender bender, they were completely fine! Not only were the phones safe from the impact, because of the raised edges on the case, the tempered glass was not even chipped.So all in all, these cases are not only great looking and stylish; they are also toddler proof, making them truly Smartish!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Have tried lots of different cases with card holders - this one is really substantially built

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 6, 2021
reviews.reviewText: This was my favourite case when I had my iPhone 7 Plus. Couldn’t part with the case for my new iPhone 13, I love how easy it is to get my cards out and the case comfortably fits 3. Pop Sockets not included.Also I’ve already dropped my new phone a couple times on concrete and it was all ok!

reviews.reviewTitle: Exactly like the equivalent product for other models
reviews.reviewText: Some improvements from previous iPhone model cases (ie some grip texture around the edge). Fits right, doesn’t slip off. Ability to place protective glass screen protector and still fit the case. Holds 3 cards & 5 bills if you wrap the bills around the middle card. Very minimal size increase over the iPhone size. Offers some protection for the camera lenses, but more importantly allows you to lay the iPhone flat with he screen up without it being lopsided by the camera lenses.
Ça ne grossi pas le téléphone, les boutons demeure accessibles et trois cartes c’est bien assez puisque les autres sont toutes dans le wallet. Plus besoin de traîner un sac ou une sacoche!
